org.javers.core.metamodel.type

Class CustomType

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.javers.core.metamodel.type.JaversType
      • org.javers.core.metamodel.type.CustomType

  • public class CustomType
extends JaversType
    Custom type in client's domain model.

    JaVers treats a custom type as a black box and doesn't take any assumptions about its content or behavior. It's a 'not modeled' type, somehow similar to unbounded wildcard type <?>.

    Values of custom type are compared by a CustomPropertyComparator and registering it (see JaversBuilder.registerCustomComparator(CustomPropertyComparator, Class) is the only way to map a custom type.

    Custom types are serialized to JSON using Gson defaults.
